flattenCoverCell(25.10)                                flattenCoverCell(25.10)

Name
       flattenCoverCell - Dissolves and flattens any instance whose master has
       class COVER, but no subclass BUMP

Syntax
       flattenCoverCell

       [-help]

       [-inst {<instanceName> | <instanceNameList>}]

       Dissolves  and  flattens any instance whose master has class COVER, but
       no subclass BUMP. You can use this command after  loading  a  DEF  file
       (after the defIn command).

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each flattenCoverCell parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man flattenCoverCell

       -inst {<instanceName> | <instanceNameList>}
              Specifies the instance, or a list of instances, to be flattened.
              If you are specifying a list, separate the instance names with a
              space.

              Default: If you do not specify  this  parameter,  all  instances
              whose masters have class COVER are flattened.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              * The  following  command  flattens the cover cells named cover-
                Cell1 and coverCell2

                flattenCoverCell -inst {coverCell1 coverCell2}

              * The following command flattens all cover cells

                flattenCoverCell

Related Information
